            <span class="text-on-surface font-semibold">A Flute</span><span class="text-secondary">~5mm</span><span class="text-secondary">Premium retail, fragile gifts</span><span class="text-secondary">High cushion</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 py-1 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="text-on-surface font-semibold">B Flute</span><span class="text-secondary">~3mm</span><span class="text-secondary">Canned goods, retail, pizza boxes</span><span class="text-secondary">Good puncture resist.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 py-1 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="text-on-surface font-semibold">C Flute</span><span class="text-secondary">~4mm</span><span class="text-secondary">General shipping, most e-commerce</span><span class="text-secondary">Balanced all-rounder</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 py-1 border-b border-outline-variant/20">
            <span class="text-on-surface font-semibold">E Flute</span><span class="text-secondary">~1.5mm</span><span class="text-secondary">Small retail boxes, inner dividers</span><span class="text-secondary">Lightweight, fine print</span>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-2 py-1">
            <span class="text-on-surface font-semibold">BC Double Wall</span><span class="text-secondary">~7mm</span><span class="text-secondary">Heavy goods, industrial, exports</span><span class="text-secondary">Very high compression</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">A Flute: Maximum Cushioning</h2>
      <p>A flute is the thickest single-wall corrugated (approximately 5mm), with the largest wave size. It has the best cushioning and stacking strength of single-wall options, making it popular for premium retail packaging, wine and spirits, and fragile gift items. It is slightly more expensive due to more fluting material per sheet. Not commonly used for basic e-commerce shipping in Malaysia where B and C flute dominate.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">B Flute: Puncture Resistance & Versatility</h2>
      <p>B flute (around 3mm) has smaller, more tightly packed waves, giving it excellent puncture resistance and a flatter surface that prints well. It is the standard for canned goods, hardware retail boxes, and food packaging boxes in Malaysia. Its lower profile also means more boxes per pallet for storage efficiency. B flute is commonly used in manufacturing operations where boxes are run through automated filling lines.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">C Flute: The Malaysian Standard for E-Commerce</h2>
      <p>C flute (around 4mm) is the most widely used flute in Malaysia's e-commerce and general distribution sector. It balances cushioning, compressive strength, and cost more effectively than any other single-wall type. For most products under 10 kg shipped via J&T, Ninja Van, Pos Laju, or DHL, C flute single wall is the appropriate choice. When in doubt, C flute is where to start.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">BC Double Wall: Industrial & Export Grade</h2>
      <p>BC double wall combines B flute and C flute layers, giving approximately 7mm total thickness and dramatically higher compressive strength. It is the standard for machinery parts, export cartons, heavy automotive components, and warehouse master cartons. BC flute can support very high stack loads and withstands the rigours of sea freight. It is heavier and more expensive than single wall but justified for products where damage cost exceeds the packaging premium.</p>

